                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Vera Cruz</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-24T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1912—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No foreigners hurt or property destroyed. City in the possession of Federals.
                    Díaz is a prisoner; if asylum is asked for will be refused.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
